      Place item blocks from the given source in the world.
      Parameters:
      network - The network in which the movement is happening.
      ingredientsNetwork - The ingredients network in which the movement is happening.
      channel - The channel.
      connection - The connection object.
      source - The source item storage.
      world - The destination world.
      pos - The destination position.
      side - The destination side.
      itemStackMatcher - The itemstack match predicate.
      hand - The hand to place the block with.
      blockUpdate - If a block update should occur after placement.
      ignoreReplacable - If replacable blocks should be overriden when placing blocks.
      craftIfFailed - If the exact ingredient from ingredientPredicate should be crafted if transfer failed.
      Returns:
      The placed item.
      Throws:
      org.cyclops.integrateddynamics.api.evaluate.EvaluationException - If illegal movement occured and further movement should stop.
